Vice President Kamala Harris addressed the National Education Association (NEA) at the McCormick Place Convention Center in Chicago. She expressed her condolences for the victims of a recent shooting in Highland Park and called for an end to gun violence. Harris highlighted the need for stronger gun safety laws, including renewing the assault weapons ban and repealing the liability shield for gun manufacturers. She praised the NEA for their dedication as educators and emphasized the importance of their work in shaping policies. Harris discussed the administration's efforts to support education, including funding through the American Rescue Plan and the Bipartisan Infrastructure Law. She acknowledged the obstacles faced by unions and pledged to lead the most pro-union administration in American history. Harris criticized Republican leaders for their opposition to progressive policies and urged them to attend a civics lesson. She concluded by emphasizing the importance of unity and vigilance in the fight for progress.